Officials have said up to 45 people, including eight soldiers, were killed in the clashes between the Frontier Corps troops and Bugti tribesmen, who dominate Dera Bugti.
 Nawab Akbar Bugti, the chief of Bugti tribe in Dera Bugti, claimed that hundreds of his armed supporters have taken up positions on mountains near the town and they were ready to face the security forces.
 Thousands of troops moved into Baluchistan after a rocket barrage on the gas plant left eight people dead in January.